Tim Rawling <trawling(-at-)unimelb.edu.au> wrote:
> When I turn the key the solenoid clicks and then a
> second or so passes before the starter (very slowly)
turns the engine over<<
 
Sounds like it could be a grounding problem. make sure
you have a good ground from the strap that grounds the
tranny to the body of the bus, and the battery
negative to the body of the bus.


